    <title>Refugees contributor: Vladislav Chirin, Zineb Doubli and Patrick Martin</title>
    <description>Vladislav Chirin is a student of international journalism at St Petersburg State University.
Patrick Martin studied civil engineering at the University of Notre Dame. He then served in the U.S. Marine Corps and deployed to Afghanistan twice. He is studying video journalism and national security reporting at the Medill School of Journalism.
Zineb Doubli (born in Morocco) has been living in Germany since 2008. She is currently a master’s program student at the Hamburg University of Applied Sciences.
</description>
